        <p>
            She also got involved in children's rights, against nuclear power and in the Animal
            Protection Campaign with several debate articles in Expressen. Astrid Lindgren took over Selma Lagerlöf's place, as a motif 
            on the Swedish 20 kroner banknote, on 1 October 2015. The estimated 2019 figure for book sales is 165 million copies and they have been translated into 107 languages ​​(2019).
            [1] Many of Lindgren's books have been made into films — the majority are Swedish feature films. 
            Recurring in Lindgren's films are composer Georg Riedel, director Olle Hellbom and actor Allan Edwall. 
            A few foreign films and animations of Lindgren's books and short stories have also been produced. 
            Lindgren was awarded a large number of national and international prizes for his books, including the Swedish Academy's 
            large gold medal. 
        </p>
